    <!-- S8: HOW NODE WORKS -->
    <div class="section open" id="s8">
      <div class="section-head" onclick="toggle('s8')">
        <div class="section-num">08</div>
        <div class="section-title">How Node.js Works — Architecture Overview</div>
        <div class="section-chevron">▼</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <h3>Request-Response Cycle</h3>
        <p>When a user opens your app, here is what happens from click to response:</p>
        <div class="diagram">
          <div class="node cyan">Client (Browser / Mobile App)</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓ HTTP Request</div>
          <div class="node">Internet</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="node green">Node.js Server (your code)</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓ query</div>
          <div class="node yellow">Database (MongoDB)</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓ data returned</div>
          <div class="node green">Node.js processes &amp; formats</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓ JSON Response</div>
          <div class="node cyan">Client displays data ✅</div>
        </div>

        <h3>Non-Blocking I/O — The Magic of Node.js</h3>
        <p>Traditional servers block and wait when a database call takes 200ms. Node.js <strong>never waits</strong> — it registers a callback and moves on to handle other requests.</p>

        <div class="analogy">
          <div class="analogy-title">🍔 Analogy — Fast Food vs Fine Dining</div>
          <div class="analogy-body">
            <strong>Traditional server (blocking)</strong> = Waiter takes Order 1, stands at kitchen window, waits 10 minutes, brings Order 1, then takes Order 2.<br><br>
            <strong>Node.js (non-blocking)</strong> = Waiter takes Order 1, gives ticket to kitchen, immediately takes Order 2, Order 3, Order 4… Kitchen calls when food is ready. Waiter collects and delivers.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Node.js — Non-Blocking Example</span><span class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</span></div>
          <pre><span class="kw">const</span> <span class="var">fs</span> = <span class="fn">require</span>(<span class="str">'fs'</span>);

<span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'1. Start reading file...'</span>);

<span class="cm">// Non-blocking — does NOT wait here</span>
<span class="var">fs</span>.<span class="fn">readFile</span>(<span class="str">'data.txt'</span>, <span class="str">'utf8'</span>, (<span class="var">err</span>, <span class="var">data</span>) => {
  <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'3. File read complete!'</span>, <span class="var">data</span>);
});

<span class="cm">// This runs IMMEDIATELY, does not wait for file read</span>
<span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'2. Doing other work while file reads...'</span>);

<span class="cm">// Output order:
// 1. Start reading file...
// 2. Doing other work while file reads...
// 3. File read complete!  ← comes later, when ready</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

